[30;1m192 | [0m[35m- Numpy 1.20.0 no longer causes an import error.[0m
[30;1m193 | [0m[35m- High-level Device class inheritance now supports {class}`~tango.server.class_property`.[0m
[30;1m194 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m28 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m31 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35m- For commit messages the first line should be short (50 chars or less) and contain a summary[0m

[30;1m55 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m56 | [0m[35mThe main benefit of asynchronous programing approach is that it lets you[0m
[30;1m57 | [0m[35mcontrol precisely when code is run sequentially without interruptions and[0m
[30;1m58 | [0m[35mwhen control can be given back to the event loop. It's especially useful[0m
[30;1m59 | [0m[35mif you want to perform some long operations and don't want to prevent clients[0m
[30;1m60 | [0m[35mfrom accessing other parts of your device (attributes, in particular). This[0m
[30;1m61 | [0m[35mmeans that in {obj}`~tango.GreenMode.Asyncio` green mode there is no monitor[0m

[30;1m165 | [0m[35mthe python database API oriented to tango (I will call this TDB interface).[0m

[30;1m158 | [0m[35m   executor. I.e., `executor.submit(thread_task)`.  This is not guaranteed to work.[0m
